# 🎯 LeaveLoop — Complete Interview Preparation Guide

---

## 🗣️ HOW TO INTRODUCE THIS PROJECT TO AN INTERVIEWER

> **Read this script out loud. Practice it 3 times until it feels natural.**

---

**"I built a full-stack HR Management System called LeaveLoop. The core problem it solves is giving organizations a digital, role-based platform to manage employee leave applications and expense reimbursements — without paper forms or email chains.**

**On the backend, I built a RESTful API using Node.js and Express, with MongoDB as the database accessed through Mongoose. I implemented JWT-based authentication and a Role-Based Access Control system with three distinct roles — Admin, Manager, and Employee — each having different levels of access and UI.**

**On the frontend, I used React 18 with Vite as the build tool, React Router v7 for navigation, and Tailwind CSS for responsive styling. I also integrated Cloudinary for uploading profile photos and reimbursement receipts, and deployed the backend on Render and the frontend on Vercel.**

**The system supports the complete workflow: an employee applies for leave or submits a reimbursement, a manager reviews and approves or rejects it with notes, and an admin can manage all users in the system. I also built a dark/light theme toggle, protected route guards on the frontend, and a central error handler on the backend.**

**This project taught me how authentication flows work end-to-end, how to design RBAC systems, how to handle CORS in a real deployment scenario, and how to structure a production-ready MERN application."**

---

## 📦 TECH STACK QUICK REFERENCE

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Runtime | Node.js | JavaScript on the server |
| Framework | Express.js | HTTP server & routing |
| Database | MongoDB + Mongoose | NoSQL DB + ODM |
| Auth | JWT + bcryptjs | Token-based auth + password hashing |
| File Upload | Multer (+ Cloudinary) | Handle multipart form data |
| Frontend | React 18 + Vite | UI + fast dev build tool |
| Routing | React Router v7 | Client-side routing |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | Utility-first CSS |
| HTTP Client | Axios | Frontend API calls |
| Notifications | react-hot-toast | Toast notifications |
| Icons | lucide-react | Icon library |
| Deployment | Render (BE) + Vercel (FE) | Hosting |

